\description{
Produces publication-quality visualisations and statistical summary tables
from a \code{climasus_dlnm} object returned by \code{\link[=sus_mod_dlnm]{sus_mod_dlnm()}}. Implements all
visualisation types standard in distributed lag non-linear model (DLNM)
epidemiology: overall exposure-response, lag-response, bidimensional surface,
contour map, lag-stratified slices, exposure distribution, and time series.
}
\section{Plot types (\code{type})}{
\tabular{lll}{
   \code{type} \tab Description \tab Key reference \cr
   \code{"overall"} \tab Cumulative exposure-response curve with CI + exposure histogram \tab Gasparrini et al. (2010) \cr
   \code{"lag"} \tab Lag-specific and cumulative lag-response at a given exposure \tab Gasparrini et al. (2010) \cr
   \code{"surface"} \tab 3-D bidimensional exposure × lag response surface \tab Gasparrini (2011) \cr
   \code{"contour"} \tab 2-D contour heat map of exposure × lag (publication-friendly) \tab Gasparrini et al. (2014) \cr
   \code{"slice"} \tab Exposure-response curves at specific lag times (multilag) \tab Armstrong (2006) \cr
   \code{"distribution"} \tab Exposure variable histogram/density with quartile markers \tab Bhaskaran et al. (2013) \cr
   \code{"series"} \tab Daily outcome count + exposure time series \tab Bhaskaran et al. (2013) \cr
}
}

\section{Statistical table (\code{output_type = "table"} or \code{"all"})}{

When a table is requested, returns a \pkg{gt} object (or tibble fallback)
with four sections: (1) model specification, (2) cumulative RR at exposure
percentiles, (3) lag peak summary, and (4) model diagnostics following
reporting standards in Gasparrini et al. (2014) and Bhaskaran et al. (2013).
}

